## XAML – Using `AppThemeBinding`

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.MainPage"
             BackgroundColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=#FFFFFF, Dark=#1E1E1E}">

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="20" Spacing="16">
        <Label Text="Welcome"
               FontSize="24"
               TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=#000000, Dark=#F0F0F0}" />

        <Label Text="This page responds to your system theme."
               TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=#333333, Dark=#CCCCCC}" />

        <Button Text="Click Me"
                BackgroundColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=#6200EE, Dark=#BB86FC}"
                TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=#FFFFFF, Dark=#000000}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

`AppThemeBinding` automatically re-evaluates whenever the OS theme changes—no event wiring needed.

---

## C# Alternative – `SetAppTheme` extension method

```csharp
public class MainPage : ContentPage
{
    public MainPage()
    {
        BackgroundColor = Colors.White;
        this.SetAppTheme(BackgroundColorProperty, Colors.White, Color.FromArgb("#1E1E1E"));

        var title = new Label { Text = "Welcome", FontSize = 24 };
        title.SetAppTheme(Label.TextColorProperty, Colors.Black, Color.FromArgb("#F0F0F0"));

        var button = new Button { Text = "Click Me" };
        button.SetAppTheme(Button.BackgroundColorProperty,
            Color.FromArgb("#6200EE"), Color.FromArgb("#BB86FC"));
        button.SetAppTheme(Button.TextColorProperty, Colors.White, Colors.Black);

        Content = new VerticalStackLayout
        {
            Padding = 20, Spacing = 16,
            Children = { title, button }
        };
    }
}
```

`SetAppTheme(BindableProperty, lightValue, darkValue)` is the code-behind equivalent of `{AppThemeBinding}`.

---

### Key points

| Concern | Detail |
|---------|--------|
| **Reactivity** | Both approaches update live when the user toggles the device theme. |
| **Detection** | Read the current theme with `Application.Current.RequestedTheme` (`Light`, `Dark`, or `Unspecified`). |
| **Manual override** | Set `Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Dark;` to force a specific theme app-wide. |
| **Resources** | For larger apps, define colors in `ResourceDictionary` and reference them via `{StaticResource}` or `{DynamicResource}` combined with theme dictionaries for cleaner maintenance. |
